{{Unreferenced|date=December 2009}}
The '''German Crown Jewels''' encompass the [[Imperial Regalia]] of the [[German Kingdom]] within the [[Holy Roman Empire]] until 1806. From 1871 until 1918 the Prussians kings redenominated the [[Prussian Crown Jewels]] as Crown jewels of the [[German Emperor|German Emperors]]. Formally the [[German Empire]] had no physical Crown jewels, though a model of a [[German State Crown]] was created and used in emblems. 

The term may also be used in reference to regalia of the various constitutive [[List of historic states of Germany|German monarchies]] that sprang from the Holy Roman Empire and later were unified in the German Empire.

Since the end of the German monarchies in 1918, the regalia and jewels of the different states have been kept in museums since all of Germany remains under republican rule.

