{{EngvarB|date=August 2016}} {{Use dmy dates|date=August 2016}} {{Infobox civilian attack |title=Minna prison break |partof=[[Prison escape]] |image= Nigeria Niger State map.png |fatalities = 0 |injuries = 1 |type= Prison break |perps=[[Robbery|Armed robbers]] |target=Minna medium prison |numparts=3 |dfens=270 prisoners escaped |date= 6 December 2014 |location=[[Niger State]], Northwestern [[Nigeria]] }}
The '''Minna prison break''' was an attack on Minna medium prison, [[Minna]] in the northwestern Nigerian city of [[Niger State]] by three unknown gunmen suspected to be [[Robbery|armed robbers]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://newswirengr.com/2014/12/06/another-jailbreak-in-minna-prison-inmates-set-free/|title=Another Jailbreak in Minna Prison, Inmates Set Free|work=NewsWireNGR|accessdate=24 December 2014}}</ref> The attack occurred on 6 December 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nigerianeye.com/2014/12/another-prison-break-in-minna-niger.html?m=1|title=Another Prison Break in Minna, Niger State, 270 inmates freed, weapons stolen|work=Nigerian Eye|accessdate=24 December 2014}}</ref> 270 prisoners escaped from the prison leaving a security officer injured.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sunnewsonline.com/new/?p=94331|title=270 prisoners escape….As gunmen attack Minna prison|publisher=|accessdate=24 December 2014|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141224123601/http://sunnewsonline.com/new/?p=94331|archivedate=24 December 2014|df=dmy-all}}</ref> The escaped prisoners were largely gangs of armed robbers, awaiting trial.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ereporter.com.ng/index.php/national-news/item/1944-b-r-e-a-k-i-n-g-jailbreak-in-minna-270-inmates-freed-weapons-stolen|title=B-R-E-A-K-I-N-G: Jailbreak in Minna, 270 inmates freed, weapons stolen |author=|publisher=e-Reporter|accessdate=24 December 2014}}</ref> It was reported that one of the notorious armed robbers in the prison called Osama took part in the jail break.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mynewswatchtimesng.com/prison-break-in-minna-270-inmates-escape/|title=Prison break in Minna, 270 inmates escape|author=Justina Asishana, Minna|work=Newswatch Times|accessdate=24 December 2014}}</ref>
==Incident== The incident was reported to have occurred on Saturday, 6 December 2014, about a week after the [[Ekiti prison break]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailytrust.com.ng/sunday/index.php/news/18968-270-inmates-escape-in-minna-jail-break|title=270 inmates escape in Minna jail break|author=aliyu|work=Sunday Trust online|accessdate=24 December 2014}}</ref> The unknown gunmen, suspected to be armed robbers freed 270 inmates and also looted weapons and bullet-proof vest of the [[Nigerian Prisons Services]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://thenationonlineng.net/new/jail-break-minna-270-inmates-freed/|title=Jail break in Minna, 270 Inmates freed|author=Jide Orintunsin|work=The Nation|accessdate=24 December 2014}}</ref> About 108 of the escaped prisoners was rearrested by the [[Nigerian Prisons Services]] in conjunction with Nigerian police after the attack.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thisdaylive.com/articles/jail-break-nps-recaptures-108-inmates-of-minna-prison/196240/|title=Jail Break: NPS Recaptures 108 Inmates of Minna Prison|publisher=THISDAY LIVE|accessdate=24 December 2014|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141224110049/http://www.thisdaylive.com/articles/jail-break-nps-recaptures-108-inmates-of-minna-prison/196240/|archivedate=24 December 2014|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.punchng.com/news/minna-jailbreak-nps-recaptures-108-inmates/|title=Minna jailbreak: NPS recaptures 108 inmates|work=The Punch|accessdate=24 December 2014|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141224182232/http://www.punchng.com/news/minna-jailbreak-nps-recaptures-108-inmates/|archivedate=24 December 2014|df=dmy-all}}</ref> This incident resulted in the remover and suspension of the [[Niger State]] prison controller, Musa Maiyaki and the Officer-in-Charge of Medium Security Prison Minna, Mohammed Buena and all officers on duty on the day of the jail break by the [[Nigeria|federal government of Nigeria]] through the minister of interior [[Abba Moro]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://newtelegraphonline.com/jailbreak-moro-suspends-minna-prisons-top-officials/|title=Jailbreak: Moro suspends Minna prison’s top officials|author=|publisher=New Telegraph|accessdate=24 December 2014|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141224110022/http://newtelegraphonline.com/jailbreak-moro-suspends-minna-prisons-top-officials/|archivedate=24 December 2014|df=dmy-all}}</ref> following a recommendation by the controller general of the [[Nigerian Prisons Services]], Dr Peter Ekpendu.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://leadership.ng/news/394037/minna-jailbreak-fg-suspends-controller-officer-charge-others|title=Minna Jailbreak: FG Suspends Controller, Officer-in-charge, Others |work=Nigerian News from Leadership Newspapers|accessdate=24 December 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vanguardngr.com/2014/12/minna-jailbreak-prisons-controller-others-susoended/|title=Minna Jailbreak: Prisons Controller, others suspended|work=Vanguard News|accessdate=24 December 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://sunnewsonline.com/new/?p=94478|title=Heads may roll over Minna jailbreak|publisher=|accessdate=24 December 2014}}</ref>
