The '''Minokok''' are an [[indigenous peoples|indigenous]] [[ethnic group]] residing in [[Sabah]], [[Malaysia]]. They reside near the headwaters of [[Kinabatangan River]], in [[Sandakan Division]]. Their population was estimated at 2,000 in the year 1991. They are considered a sub-group of the [[Kadazan-Dusun]], as their language ([[ISO 639-3]] mqq) belongs to the Dusunic branch of the [[Austronesian languages|Austronesian]] language family. About 35% of the population has been converted to [[evangelical Christianity]], the remainder are [[animist]].

